 THE wait is finally over as Nigerians will now get a chance to see the substance Femi Otedola’s daughter, Temi, is made of as an actor. Starring as Moremi Oluwa in Kunle Afolayan’s Citation, the movie is now available on the popular movie site, Netflix. The pretty 23-year-old plays a lead female character alongside other A-list actors and Chairman of First Bank of Nigeria, Ibukun Awosika, who also made her acting debut. In the movie, Temi is forced to find a way to deal with an awkward situation of sexual harassment from a male lecturer, Prof. Lucien Nd’yara, a role played by Hollywood star, Jimmy-Jean Louis. She later drags Nd’yara before the University Senate.